  "texts": [
    "Table 3 also shows the distribution of codes for the resulting data set.",
    "The coding of the correspondences between learning tips and lecture topics within essays was conducted by a team of seven coders on a shared Excel sheet.",
    "This sheet contained 100 columns, one for each combination of a learning tip and a topic from the lecture (see Table 4), and rows for each essay.",
    "The coders were tasked to read the essays individually and enter a \"1\" into the respective cell if a lecture concept was linked to a given learning tip within a given essay and a \"0\" otherwise.",
    "In a pilot phase, 100 essays were coded in parallel with each of them being coded by two out of the seven coders."
  ],
